---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Technical Brief: Sovereign Public Information | OpenPublicInfo.ie">
  <main class="py-20">
    <article class="container-tight prose prose-slate max-w-none">
      <header class="mb-16 border-b-4 border-brand-text pb-8">
        <span class="text-brand-accent font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-4 block">Official Briefing Document</span>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-black uppercase leading-none mb-6">
          Sovereign Public<br/> Information Standards
        </h1>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 text-sm uppercase font-bold text-slate-500">
          <div><span class="text-slate-400">To:</span> National Transport Authority (NTA)</div>
          <div><span class="text-slate-400">Date:</span> May 2026</div>
          <div><span class="text-slate-400">Ref:</span> OPI-2026-001</div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mb-6">Executive Summary</h2>
        <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed">
          Current communication practices among Irish public transport providers frequently treat private, third-party social media platforms (specifically X/Twitter) as primary notification hubs for real-time disruptions. This creates a <strong>Two-Tier Information System</strong> that excludes citizens based on platform membership and private data tracking consent.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed">
          This brief proposes a <strong>"Source First"</strong> notification standard, mandating that state-owned digital infrastructure serves as the <strong>Single Source of Truth (SSOT)</strong> for all public interest updates.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mb-6">1. The Problem: Siloed Real-Time Data</h2>
        <p>
          While public transport providers have made strides in publishing static timetable data (GTFS), <strong>unplanned disruption data</strong> remains architecturally siloed. 
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-4">
          <li><strong>Gated Access:</strong> Vital safety and service updates are increasingly "walled off" behind social media logins.</li>
          <li><strong>Algorithmic Fragility:</strong> Chronological delivery of urgent info is now subject to private company algorithms, meaning "Live" updates are often seen hours late by users.</li>
          <li><strong>Regulatory Non-Compliance:</strong> Exclusive social media publishing fails to meet the <em>Public Sector Bodies Accessibility Regulations</em>, as these platforms are not under the control or accessibility auditing of the state.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-16 bg-slate-100 p-8 border-l-8 border-brand-text">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mb-6 italic text-brand-accent">2. The "Source First" Requirement</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6">
          We propose that all NTA-regulated bodies adopt a <strong>Source First Workflow</strong>. Architectural priority must be given to the official state domain.
        </p>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-white p-6 shadow-sm border border-slate-200">
            <h3 class="font-bold uppercase text-xs mb-2 text-slate-400 tracking-widest">Current (Broken) Workflow</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 font-mono">Incident &rarr; Manual Tweet &rarr; (Optional) Website Update &rarr; (Delayed) App Update.</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-red-600 mt-4 font-bold">Result: Data Fragmentation & Platform Gating</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 shadow-md border-t-4 border-brand-accent">
            <h3 class="font-bold uppercase text-xs mb-2 text-brand-accent tracking-widest text-brand-text">Proposed Sovereign Workflow</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-brand-text font-mono font-bold">Incident &rarr; Central CMS &rarr; Immediate Web/App/Open-API Push &rarr; Automated Social Media Mirror.</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-green-700 mt-4 font-bold text-brand-text">Result: 100% Reach & Data Integrity</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mb-6">3. Technical Architecture</h2>
        
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 uppercase tracking-tight text-slate-700">3.1 Unified Alert Ingestion (The "Hub")</h3>
        <p class="mb-6">
          The NTA should implement or mandate a <strong>Unified Alert Ingestion API</strong>. Instead of operators managing disparate social media accounts, they should interface with a single, state-owned Content Management System (CMS) designed for high-availability alert distribution.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-6 mb-8 rounded">
          <h4 class="text-sm font-black uppercase mb-3">Core CMS Requirements:</h4>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 mb-0">
            <li><strong>Atomic Updates:</strong> A single entry point for an alert that propagates to all channels simultaneously.</li>
            <li><strong>Webhook Architecture:</strong> Automated "push" notifications to official apps, RSS feeds, and social media APIs (X, Mastodon, Facebook) via server-side hooks.</li>
            <li><strong>Audit Logging:</strong> A transparent, publicly accessible log of all alerts, ensuring accountability for service failures.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 uppercase tracking-tight text-slate-700">3.2 Standardized Data Exports (The "Spokes")</h3>
        <p class="mb-6">
          To ensure platform neutrality, the data must be exported in standardized, non-proprietary formats:
        </p>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div class="border-t border-slate-200 pt-4">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-brand-text uppercase text-sm mb-2 italic tracking-widest text-brand-accent underline underline-offset-4 decoration-2">GTFS-Realtime (Service Alerts)</h4>
            <p class="text-sm">The industry standard for real-time transit info. Mandating the full use of the <code>ServiceAlerts</code> feed ensures that Google Maps, Apple Maps, and independent apps show the <strong>exact same data</strong> as the official site.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-t border-slate-200 pt-4">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-brand-text uppercase text-sm mb-2 italic tracking-widest text-brand-accent underline underline-offset-4 decoration-2 text-brand-accent">Sovereign RSS/Atom</h4>
            <p class="text-sm">A "low-tech" but highly accessible standard. RSS allows local community groups, radio stations, and individual developers to subscribe to alerts without API keys or complex integrations.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 uppercase tracking-tight text-slate-700">3.3 The "Mirror" Model for Social Media</h3>
        <p>
          Social media should function purely as a <strong>read-only mirror</strong> of the official CMS. Operators should be discouraged from manual "Twitter-only" commentary. Any detail provided on social media must, by definition, be a subset of the detail available on the official state-owned SSOT.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-16 border-t-4 border-slate-200 pt-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mb-6">Recommendations</h2>
        <ol class="space-y-6">
          <li class="pl-4">
            <strong>Mandate SSOT:</strong> Legally require all state-funded bodies to publish real-time alerts to their own domain <em>prior to</em> or <em>simultaneous with</em> third-party networks.
          </li>
          <li class="pl-4">
            <strong>Audit Accessibility:</strong> Conduct a formal audit of how social-media-first communication excludes citizens with disabilities and the elderly.
          </li>
          <li class="pl-4">
            <strong>Standardize Open Feeds:</strong> Provide a unified API endpoint for all NTA-regulated service alerts.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <footer class="mt-24 pt-12 border-t border-slate-200 text-slate-500 italic">
        <p>This document was drafted by the OpenPublicInfo.ie initiative. For technical consultation or further briefing, contact <a href="mailto:munim2020@gmail.com" class="text-brand-accent underline">Munim Kazia</a>.</p>
      </footer>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
